  "id": "019cfaf7-e6e3-7d03-bc6a-b2af0c23e1ad",
  "content": "## 02_claude_scene_analysis.py — Implementation Complete\n\nPhase 2 scene analysis script implemented at `scripts/02_claude_scene_analysis.py`. Key design decisions:\n\n### Architecture\n- Single-file implementation following 01_extract_frames.py patterns (workspace root resolution, config loading, logging format)\n- Pass 1 only implemented (all keyframes sent in batches). Pass 2 refinement deferred — keyframe-level precision used for first_appearance_frame since original footage frames aren't available at this stage.\n\n### Batching Logic\n- Keyframes sorted by frame number, split into batches of `claude_batch_size` (default 12 from config)\n- Previously-identified subjects accumulated across batches and passed to subsequent Claude calls so it knows what's already tracked\n- This prevents duplicate subject reporting across batches within a clip\n\n### Claude API Integration\n- System prompt instructs Claude to identify marine life (species-level), divers, and notable coral/terrain\n- Returns JSON array of subjects with label, bbox_normalised [x_min, y_min, x_max, y_max] (0-1), first_appearance_frame, confidence (high/medium/low)\n- Response parsing handles markdown code block wrapping (```json...```)\n- Validation enforces schema: 4-element bbox with 0-1 values, valid confidence levels\n\n### Output Schema\n```json\n{\"clip_id\": \"DJI_0042\", \"subjects\": [{\"label\": \"napoleon_wrasse\", \"first_appearance_frame\": 14, \"bbox_normalised\": [0.3, 0.2, 0.7, 0.8], \"confidence\": \"high\"}]}\n```\n\n### Error Handling\n- Missing API key: exit with clear error (but allowed in --dry-run)\n- API call failure: log error and continue with remaining batches\n- Unparseable JSON: log raw response and skip batch\n- No keyframes found: exit with error pointing to Phase 1\n\n### Config Keys Used\n- `anthropic_api_key` / `$ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` env var\n- `claude_model` (default: claude-sonnet-4-6)\n- `claude_batch_size` (default: 12)\n- `working_dir` (for keyframes input and scene_analysis output)\n\n### CLI\n- `--date YYYY-MM-DD` (required)\n- `--dry-run` — shows batching plan and cost estimates without API calls\n- `--verbose` / `-v` — debug logging",
